title: Haniyeh urges Palestinians to march on Al-Aqsa Mosque on 1st day of Ramadan
description: Ismail Haniyeh, the political bureau chief of Hamas, has called on the Palestinians in the occupied West Bank to march on Al-Aqsa Mosque on the first day of the Muslim holy month of Ramadan.

title: UN: One quarter of Gaza's people one step away from famine
description: At least 576,000 people in the Gaza Strip - one quarter of the population - are one step away from famine, a senior UN aid official told the Security Council on Tuesday, warning that widespread famine could be "almost inevitable" without action.

title: Russia: West allows Israel to use hunger as a method of war
description: The U.S. and Russian representatives to the UN exchanged heated words Tuesday during a Security Council session on Gaza.

title: Save the Children: Israel is killing kids in “slow motion”
description: Children in Gaza are on the brink of starvation while food aid sits just across the border, Alexandra Saieh of Save the Children warned.

title: Iran lambasts foreign intervention in Syria as violation of international law
description: TEHRAN - Iran's Ambassador and Permanent Representative to the United Nations Amir Saeid Iravani says terrorism and the ongoing Zionist attacks on Syria are a flagrant violation of international law.

title: Iran, Turkmenistan vow to strengthen ties at consular session
description: TEHRAN – The 16th session of the intergovernmental Turkmen-Iranian commission was held on Tuesday where the two sides emphasized the importance of past agreements and explored new avenues for cooperation.

title: Preparations for Iran's March 1 elections fully underway: Raisi
description: TEHRAN- Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi affirms the nation's readiness to proceed with the electoral process during a cabinet meeting on Wednesday.

title: Iran will launch Pars 1 satellite Thursday morning
description: TEHRAN- Iranian Minister of Information and Communication Technology, Issa Zarepour, announced that the domestically developed Pars 1 satellite is scheduled for launch on Thursday.

title: Diverse backgrounds represented among Iran parliamentary candidates: official
description: TEHRAN – On Wednesday, the spokesperson for Iran’s Guardian Council informed journalists that the candidates running for seats in Iran’s Parliament on Friday hail from diverse professional and religious backgrounds.

title: Israel's electoral dream
description: TEHRAN- In a recent editorial piece published by The Jerusalem Post, a concerted effort was made to sow seeds of hopelessness within the Iranian populace, casting doubt on the democratic processes in Iran.

title: Tehran criticizes German FM over comments on human rights
description: TEHRAN- German Foreign Minister Annalena Baerbock’s accusations against the Islamic Republic were categorically rejected by Iran as an inane attempt by the Berlin government to hide its backing for the Israeli occupation and its indifference to egregious human rights violations occurring throughout Palestinian territory.

title: Terrorist killed while preparing for attack in southeastern Iran
description: TEHRAN – A terrorist accidently killed himself while attempting to plant bombs in a vehicle in the southeastern province of Sistan and Balouchestan, according to local authorities.

title: Nuclear messages exchanged between Tehran, Washington: Iran FM
description: TEHRAN- Iranian Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian has noted that Tehran and Washington have exchanged messages regarding the stalled nuclear talks.

title: Russian Deputy PM meets with Iran’s VP in Tehran
description: TEHRAN - In a diplomatic visit to Tehran, Alexander Novak, the Deputy Prime Minister of Russia, convened with Mohammad Mokhber, Iran's First Vice President, for discussions on various aspects of mutual interest, addressing diplomatic, economic, and strategic matters.

title: Global calls grow for sanctions on Tel Aviv
description: TEHRAN - Imposing sanctions on the Israeli regime has been a long-held demand by many in the international community over the past decades despite persistent shielding of the regime by the United States. The issue of punitive measures is being raised once more amid the devastating and indiscriminate Israeli war on Gaza.

title: North Gaza hospital shuts down surgery department
description: Gaza’s al-Awda Hospital, one of the few partially functioning health facilities left in the north, has had to cancel all surgical operations after two of its operating rooms were “targeted and destroyed”, according to its acting director Mohamed Salha.

title: Delusional post-war Gaza scenarios
description: TEHRAN- Soon after Israel launched its brutal onslaught on the Gaza Strip in early October, post-war scenarios came to the fore.

title: Aaron: An eternal flame
description: TEHRAN - The self-immolation of a 25-year-old US airman on February 25 outside the Israeli embassy in Washington DC is a solitary act of deep moral outrage against the Western complicity in the Gaza tragedy.

title: Enemies afraid of electoral miracle in Iran
description: TEHRAN- Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyed Ali Khamenei met with a number of first-time voters as well as the honorable families of martyrs on Wednesday.

title: Tehran museum to screen restored version of Kiarostami’s “Through the Olive Trees”
description: TEHRAN-The cinematheque of the Tehran Museum of Contemporary Art is set to screen a restored version of the renowned Iranian director Abbas Kiarostami’s film “Through the Olive Trees”.

title: No resolution will be issued against Iran
description: TEHRAN - The Iran newspaper pointed to Iran's nuclear issue.

title: Persepolis victorious over Zob Ahan: PGPL
description: TEHRAN – Persepolis football team defeated Zob Ahan 1-0 in the 2023/24 Iran Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL) on Wednesday.

title: Tehran’s Vahdat Hall to host mugham music concert
description: TEHRAN-Tehran’s Vahdat Hall will be hosting a mugham music concert on March 11.

title: Keyvan Saket, Tsumuzi to perform in Japan
description: TEHRAN-Iranian tar and setar virtuoso Keyvan Saket and Japanese violinist Tsumuzi are set to perform in Tokyo, Japan, in March.

title: Maestro Tjeknavorian unveils musical tribute to Maryam Mirzakhani
description: TEHRAN- Maestro Loris Tjeknavorian has released a musical creation dedicated to the late Iranian mathematician, Maryam Mirzakhani.

title: Iran, Russia ink several co-op MOUs to wrap up 17th Joint Economic Commission
description: TEHRAN – Iran and Russia signed several memorandums of understanding (MOUs) to cooperate in various sectors at the end of the two countries' 17th Joint Economic Committee meeting which was held in Tehran during February 26-28.

title: Persian New Year: Tehran gets ready to welcome visitors
description: TEHRAN – As preparations unfold for the spring holidays and Ramadan coinciding with Nowruz, Tehran’s tourism chief has revealed plans to serve visitors in the best way possible.

description: TEHRAN – A historical brick kiln and a centuries-old Hammam (public bathhouse) have recently been registered in Iran’s national list for cultural heritage.

title: Isfahan’s lesser-known sites to enchant Nowruz vacationers
description: TEHRAN – For the upcoming Nowruz vacations, Isfahan seeks to put the spotlight on its lesser-known destinations for travelers visiting the historical city situated in the heart of the Iranian plateau.

title: Roscosmos points out the interest of BRICS countries in coordinating space activities
description: Russia's BRICS partners are interested in coordinating space activities. This was stated by Yury Borisov, Director General of The Federal Space Agency (Roscosmos), in an interview with the " Pro Cosmos" portal.

title: Russian representative in Iran sees no obstacle to visa-free agreement dedicated to group travelers
description: TEHRAN - A representative of the Ministry of Economic Development of the Russian Federation in Iran has dismissed any issues regarding the implementation of the cancellation of group travel visas between the two nations.

title: Large-scale park forum to be held in April in Russia – BRICS format
description: On April 3-4, 2024, the Moscow exhibition complex Expocentre will host a park forum uniting several industry projects. These are the first International Park Forum of BRICS countries, the IV International Exhibition and Conference on creation, maintenance and development of comfortable urban environment, recreation parks, public spaces and specially protected natural areas ParkSeason Expo and the first All-Russian meeting of park directors.

title: Chinese joyful encounters in Iran vs. negative media portrayals
description: TEHRAN – A recent visit to Iran by a group of Chinese social media influencers has sparked discussions about their fresh perceptions of the country along with their people’s common stereotypes about Iran.

title: Iran aims to produce world’s first vaccine for leishmaniasis
description: TEHRAN –Pasteur Institute of Iran has embarked on producing a vaccine for leishmaniasis which is said to be the first of its kind in the world.

title: IRCS provides aid to people hit by winter storms
description: TEHRAN –The Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS) rescued 13,249 individuals affected by winter storms over February 24 – 28.

title: Tehran, Moscow to boost co-op in health sector
description: TEHRAN – Deputy Health Minister Mohammad-Hossein Niknam and his Russian counterpart Sergei Glagolev met in Tehran on Tuesday, discussing ways to enhance collaboration between the two countries in the field of health.

title: Iran Health Expo 2024 slated for May
description: TEHRAN –The 25th international exhibition of medical, dental, pharmaceutical, and laboratory equipment (Iran Health Expo 2024) will be held from May 18-21 at the Tehran Permanent International Fairgrounds.

title: See Iran
description: TEHRAN- Join us to uncover Iran’s travel gems and its vibrant cultural heritage in the following selection of stories published by the Tehran Times.

title: TEDPIX rises 8,700 points on Wednesday
description: TEHRAN- TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), rose 8,723 points to 2,054,739 on Wednesday, which is the fifth day of the Iranian calendar week.

title: IFO negotiating fishery knowledge transfer with UNIDO
description: TEHRAN – The head of the Iranian Fisheries Organization (IFO) has emphasized the use of new technologies in the fishing industry and said: “We have entered into negotiations with the United Nations Industrial Development Organization (UNIDO) to transfer new technologies in all areas from fishing to processing.”

title: Iran ranking improves 6 places among ISO members
description: TEHRAN – The head of the Institute of Standards and Industrial Research of Iran has said the country’s ranking among the 168 member countries of the International Standard Organization (ISO) has improved from 26th to 20th place.

title: TPO to hold conference on Iran-Syria trade opportunities next week
description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Trade Promotion Organization (TPO) is going to hold a conference on Syria’s trade opportunities for Iranian business operators on Sunday, March 3, an official with the organization announced.

title: Exports from Mazandaran Province grows 13% in 11 months
description: TEHRAN - More than $282 million worth of non-oil products were exported from Iran’s northern Mazandaran province in the first 11 months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21, 2023-February 21, 2024), showing a 13 percent growth compared to the same period last year, an official with the province’s customs office announced.

title: Iran’s oil sector annual growth doubles despite sanctions
description: TEHRAN - Iran’s oil sector has witnessed a twofold increase in its annual economic growth in autumn 2023, the country’s Finance and Economic Affairs said on Tuesday.

title: Natural gas consumption hits new record high
description: TEHRAN – Following the significant temperature drop over the past few days, the consumption of natural gas by Iranian domestic and commercial sectors reached 665 million cubic meters (mcm) to register a new record high in the current Iranian calendar year (ends on March 19), an official with the National Iranian Gas Company (NIGC) announced.

title: IAC preparing comprehensive document on use of smart systems in airports
description: TEHRAN – Iran Airport Company (IAC) is going to form a specialized committee to explore ways of developing the digital and electronic infrastructure of the country’s airports and aviation systems with a focus on compiling a comprehensive document on the use of smart systems in airports.

title: Wrestler Mohammadali Geraei has suspension lifted by UWW
description: TEHRAN – Iranian Greco-Roman wrestler Mohammadali Geraei is no longer suspended.

description: TEHRAN – Mohammad Tavakol, honorary member of the United World Wrestling (UWW), died on Wednesday at the age of 89.

title: Gaza ceasefire necessary for regional security
Mauricio Motta Paes named Iran volleyball coach
description: TEHRAN – Brazilian coach Mauricio Motta Paes has been named as new head coach of Iran’s men’s national volleyball team, the volleyball federation of Iran announced on Wednesday.
